<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
The type locality is likely in the Dept. Cuzco, given the addition of &quot;la 
<normalizedToken originalValue="vallée">vallee</normalizedToken>
de Santa-Anna&quot;; however, it is not mentioned in modern gazetteers. The species was described from specimens denuded of the periostracum. The figured specimen has a trace of it remaining, which suggests the colour pattern described above. Size and shape are very similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Orthalicidae" genus="Kara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kara yanamensis" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="yanamensis">Kara yanamensis</taxonomicName>
(Morelet, 1863), and the variation and distribution of these two taxa need further study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
